css- Cascading stylesheet
used for style and color

syntax
selector{
    property:value;
}
selector --> html tag or id(#) or class(.) 
#heading 
.uname
h1{
    color:red;
    }
    #heading {
        color:red;
    }
    .uname{
        color:green;
    }
    3ways css:
    1.Internal css
    2.External css-we can use <link> for this
    3.Inline css- we use html tags like
        <html tag>style</html>
        <h1 style="color: lime;"></h1>
    